GauPro: Gaussian Process Fitting

Fits a Gaussian process model to data. Gaussian processes are commonly used
in computer experiments to fit an interpolating model. The model is stored
as an 'R6' object and can be easily updated with new data. There are
options to run in parallel, and 'Rcpp' has been used to speed up
calculations. For more info about Gaussian process software, see Erickson
et al. (2018) &lt;<a href="https://doi.org/10.1016%2Fj.ejor.2017.10.002"
target="_top">doi:10.1016/j.ejor.2017.10.002</a>&gt;.
